# Azure DevOps — pipelines on Azure Repos `dev`

Pipelines are wired to **Azure Repos**, not GitHub `origin`. Still: **`git push origin` is mandatory** for this monorepo so GitHub stays current; Azure sync is **additional** for CI.

| Folder in this monorepo | Azure DevOps repo |
|-------------------------|-------------------|
| `apps/alert-theleetclub-com/` | `https://dev.azure.com/leetclub/Leet%20Monitor/_git/alert` |
| `monitoring-app-v2/` | `https://dev.azure.com/leetclub/Leet%20Monitor/_git/monitoring-app-v2` |
| `people-analytics-sync/` | `https://dev.azure.com/leetclub/Leet%20Monitor/_git/people-analytics-sync` |

## Mandatory for the agent (unless the user says **skip push**)

After changing files under **any** of the three folders above (or other monorepo edits you committed in the same session):

1. **`git status` / `git add` / `git commit`** in this monorepo (clear message).

2. **`git push origin`** (or the branch’s upstream, usually **`main`**) from repo root — **WSL bash** if Windows breaks `git`. This is the **normal monorepo push**; do **not** leave `main` only local while claiming the session is done.

3. **Mirror to Azure Repos branch `dev`** for each product tree you touched — **prefer the sync script** (clone + rsync + **normal `git push`** — fast, reliable). From repo root in **WSL**:

   ```bash
   bash scripts/sync-to-azure-dev.sh alert apps/alert-theleetclub-com
   bash scripts/sync-to-azure-dev.sh monitoring-app-v2 monitoring-app-v2
   bash scripts/sync-to-azure-dev.sh people-analytics-sync people-analytics-sync
   ```

   Run **only the line(s)** for the folder(s) you changed. Full mapping and auth: **`azure-repos-sync-from-monorepo.mdc`**. PAT: repo-root **`azure.txt`** (via **`scripts/ado-curl-auth.sh`**). **Do not** paste the PAT in chat.

4. **Pipelines:** `dev` is what **`azure-pipelines.yml`** triggers on in each Azure repo — **not** `main` unless you changed pipelines.

5. **Do not treat `git push origin` alone as “Azure / CI done”.** Origin does **not** replace step 3. Conversely, **do not** skip **`git push origin`** just because you ran Azure sync.

6. **Fallback (slow):** If **`sync-to-azure-dev.sh`** cannot be used, **`bash scripts/push-to-azure-repos.sh`** (`git subtree push`) is a last resort — it can take a long time and look stuck; see script for remotes **`ado-alert`**, **`ado-v2`**, **`ado-people`**.

7. If either push fails: print the **exact** error (no credentials). Do not assume the pipeline ran.

**Do not** run `docker` / `kubectl` for these products unless the user explicitly asks.

Legacy GAS (`monitoring-app-v1/`) still follows **`deploy-gas-and-people-api.mdc`** where applicable.
